We model spontaneous respiration using three components [25]: central chemoreflex drive (Dc), peripheral chemoreflex drive (Dp), and a wakefulness drive (Dw), quantified in litres/min. The sum of the three describes the overall desired minute ventilation of the patient (Ve,patient).
